    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As Draemon says, the closest that Java comes to inline arrays is <code>new String[]{\"blah\", \"hey\", \"yo\"}</code> however there is a neat trick that allows you to do something like</p>\n\n<p><code>array(\"blah\", \"hey\", \"yo\")</code> with the type automatically inferred.</p>\n\n<p>I have been working on a useful API for augmenting the Java language to allow for inline arrays and collection types. For more details google project Espresso4J or check it out <a href=\"http://portfolio.planetjon.ca/projects/espresso4j/\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a></p>\n"
  }, {
