  "title" : "Any way to declare an array in-line?",
  "body" : "<p>Let's say I have a method <code>m()</code> that takes an array of strings as an argument. Is there a way I can just declare this array in-line when I make the call, i.e. instead of</p>\n<pre><code>String[] strs = {&quot;blah&quot;, &quot;hey&quot;, &quot;yo&quot;};\nm(strs);\n</code></pre>\n<p>Can I just replace this with one line, and avoid declaring a named variable that I'm never going to use?</p>\n"
